<body>
Reports a variable that is declared in one <code>case</code> clause of a <code>switch</code> statement but is used in another <code>case</code>
clause of the same statement.
For block-scoped variables, this results in throwing a <code>ReferenceError</code>.
For <code>var</code> variables, it indicates a potential error. <p>Disable the inspection for <code>var</code> variables if this pattern is used intentionally.</p>
